      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mayoral Marriage: Public or Private?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Chong letter says Mayor Rudolph Giuliani's private life is his own but his 'relationship' with staff member is fair game for public examination</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani's private life is his own, but his ''relationship'' with a staff member is fair game for examination (front page, May 11). Two questions arise from his relationship with a staff member.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani's private life is his own, but his ''relationship'' with a staff member is fair game for examination (front page, May 11). Two questions arise from his relationship with a staff member.</p>
        <p>Did that staff member use her  gender to further her career, and is Mayor Giuliani's behavior acceptable to the Republican Party, a party that places great emphasis on ''family values''?</p>
        <p>PETER CHONG  Brooklyn, May 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
